The paper deals with information dissemination problems in dynamic radio networks, which are typically studied in the computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also presents algorithms for transforming single-message broadcast algorithms into multi-message broadcast algorithms, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms commonly studied in the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also discusses the optimality of the proposed algorithms, which is a topic commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
